{"key":"post-15628928","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15628928</id>\n<content>I'm disappointed people kept answering what it means to 'simmer' as if you were cooking spaghetti sauce.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You don't simmer with pf tek.&amp;nbsp; You're supposed to BOIL, because it's the steam which sterilizes, not the hot water.&amp;nbsp; Your jars should be elevated out of the water, and the steam is what does the work.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You're supposed to leave the stove on high until steam escapes from your tight fitting lid on the pot.&amp;nbsp; Then, you reduce the stove to the lowest setting which will keep steam escaping, which means the water will still be in a rapid boil during the whole process.&amp;nbsp; You'll just have to experiment to find that setting, but if no steam is escaping from under the lid, no sterilization is taking place.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Add water if necessary during the process to prevent the pot boiling dry.&amp;nbsp; It helps to have a second pot of water boiling, so you can pour already hot water in if needed.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I suggest you watch all four &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;brf tek videos&lt;/a&gt; before proceeding further.&amp;nbsp; They demonstrate the whole process.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15629281</next>\n<prev>15628300</prev>\n<first>15627879</first>\n<last>15629294</last>\n<when>1325943978</when>\n<utime>01/07/12 03:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}